ce:section.ce:para:
In this paper, a new sensitive and selective electrochemical sensor for BPA was developed based on GCE that coated with N, S-GQDs and AuNPs. By virtue of the conformational change of the aptamer after combining with BPA, the electronegativity of the electrode surface was enhanced and the electron channel reduced. Finally, sensitive detection of BPA was achieved according to the current change on probe. Under the optimum condition, results showed that N, S-GQDs had the strongest fluorescence emission under the excitation light of 350 nm, and the AuNPs introduced effectively accelerated the electron transfer and current generation, which made the sensor good conductivity. The activation surface area of the sensor was three times of the bare GCE. By calculating the electrochemical kinetic parameters such as standard rate constant (k), electron transfer coefficient (α) [36], diffusion coefficient (D) and surface concentration (Г

                        0
                     ), it is known that the prepared electrochemically aptamer sensor has good performance. DPV test with different concentrations of BPA was carried out, and the linear range of the detection was 0.1–10 μM with a detection limit of 0.03 μM. Current change of the sensor to BPA reached 28.25% in the solution with multiple interfering ions, which indicated that the sensor was highly selective. In addition, this sensor was successfully applied for the detection of BPA in tap water samples and a better recovery effect was achieved.
